standing social policy at the macro-level - a comparative approach to welfare states globally - an overview of new ways to organise and steer welfare states - an introduction to welfare state politics and underlying economic framework - an account of equality and inequality in modern societies - new directions for welfare states The book's focus on core concepts and the variety of international welfare state regimes and mechanisms for delivering social policy provides a much needed introduction to the rapidly changing concept of welfare for students on social policy, social studies, sociology and politics courses."--cProvided by publisher.  a16 29 43 0aWelfare state. 0aState, The. 0aSocial policy. 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspects.  aJC 479 G748 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035211224  aJC 479 G748 2015wLCc1i0162035211224lON_SHELFmUAAUGp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu1/9/2015  aJC 479 G748 2015wLCc1i0162035225471d12/2/2015e11/21/2015lON_SHELFmUAHSSn2p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu1/21/2015  aJC479 .G748 2015wLCc1i1007401027d3/12/2015lON_SHELFmGR_MACEWANp$58.80rYsYtBOOKu3/3/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n88212762bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/20859214